Toy Craft Tales SQL Project Create Database CREATE DATABASE ToyCraftTales; USE ToyCraftTales; Create Table CREATE TABLE toy_sales (     product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,     product_name VARCHAR(100),     category VARCHAR(50),     manufacturing_cost DECIMAL(10,2),     selling_price DECIMAL(10,2),     quantity_sold INT,     region VARCHAR(50),     sales_date DATE ); Insert Sample Data INSERT INTO toy_sales VALUES (1, 'Building Blocks', 'Educational', 150.00, 250.00, 120, 'South', '2025-01-10'), (2, 'Remote Car', 'Electronic', 500.00, 800.00, 75, 'North', '2025-01-15'), (3, 'Teddy Bear', 'Soft Toys', 200.00, 350.00, 150, 'East', '2025-02-01'), (4, 'Puzzle Game', 'Educational', 100.00, 200.00, 90, 'West', '2025-02-10'), (5, 'Drone Toy', 'Electronic', 1000.00, 1500.00, 40, 'South', '2025-02-15'); Analysis Queries 1. Total Revenue SELECT SUM(selling_price * quantity_sold) AS Total_Revenue FROM toy_sales; 2. Total Profit SELECT  SUM((selling_price - manufacturing_cost) * quantity_sold) AS Total_Profit FROM toy_sales; 3. Top Selling Category SELECT category, SUM(quantity_sold) AS Total_Quantity FROM toy_sales GROUP BY category ORDER BY Total_Quantity DESC; 4. Region Wise Sales SELECT region, SUM(selling_price * quantity_sold) AS Region_Revenue FROM toy_sales GROUP BY region; 5. Monthly Sales Trend SELECT MONTH(sales_date) AS Month, SUM(selling_price * quantity_sold) AS Monthly_Revenue FROM toy_sales GROUP BY MONTH(sales_date) ORDER BY Month; How This Helps in Tableau You can: Connect Tableau to MySQL Import toy_sales table Create: Bar Chart (Category vs Sales) Line Chart (Monthly Trend) Pie Chart (Region Share) Profit Analysis Dashboard If you want, I can also give:

Toy Craft Tales SQL Project Create Database CREATE DATABASE ToyCraftTales; USE ToyCraftTales; Create Table CREATE TABLE toy_sales ( product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(100), category VARCHAR(50), manufacturing_cost DECIMAL(10,2), selling_price DECIMAL(10,2), quantity_sold INT, region VARCHAR(50), sales_date DATE ); Insert Sample Data INSERT INTO toy_sales VALUES (1, 'Building Blocks', 'Educational', 150.00, 250.00, 120, 'South', '2025-01-10'), (2, 'Remote Car', 'Electronic', 500.00, 800.00, 75, 'North', '2025-01-15'), (3, 'Teddy Bear', 'Soft Toys', 200.00, 350.00, 150, 'East', '2025-02-01'), (4, 'Puzzle Game', 'Educational', 100.00, 200.00, 90, 'West', '2025-02-10'), (5, 'Drone Toy', 'Electronic', 1000.00, 1500.00, 40, 'South', '2025-02-15'); Analysis Queries 1. Total Revenue SELECT SUM(selling_price * quantity_sold) AS Total_Revenue FROM toy_sales; 2. Total Profit SELECT SUM((selling_price - manufacturing_cost) * quantity_sold) AS Total_Profit FROM toy_sales; 3. Top Selling Category SELECT category, SUM(quantity_sold) AS Total_Quantity FROM toy_sales GROUP BY category ORDER BY Total_Quantity DESC; 4. Region Wise Sales SELECT region, SUM(selling_price * quantity_sold) AS Region_Revenue FROM toy_sales GROUP BY region; 5. Monthly Sales Trend SELECT MONTH(sales_date) AS Month, SUM(selling_price * quantity_sold) AS Monthly_Revenue FROM toy_sales GROUP BY MONTH(sales_date) ORDER BY Month; How This Helps in Tableau You can: Connect Tableau to MySQL Import toy_sales table Create: Bar Chart (Category vs Sales) Line Chart (Monthly Trend) Pie Chart (Region Share) Profit Analysis Dashboard If you want, I can also give:6:55 PM
